Two people yesterday died on the spot when their motorcycle rammed a tractor that had collided head-on with a lorry at Ebwaliro on the Ekero-Sabatia road.
 The driver of the tractor had lost control of the vehicle after its brakes failed. 
 ALSO READ:

Jaguar reacts after his vehicle is involved in multiple car crash (Photos)

 The motorcycle rider is admitted to hospital in a critical condition. According to Dennis Mukolwe, a witness, the rider of the motorcycle was heading to Sabatia when he hit the tractor.
 The bodies were moved to St Mary's Hospital mortuary.




